<P>As the world's largest mobile electronics show, CES gives the industry its first glimpses of the new mobile electronics products that make car travel safer, more fun and more productive.</P>
<P>New automobile information technology let you use your travel time to better manage your home life and your work life.  Car PC products help you get contact and address information by voice recognition, or learn the latest news through their numeric paging and e-mail alerts, take voice memos, or even share files with desktop PCs and palmtops.</P>
<P>New mobile electronics products can help you protect yourself, your family and your property. Integrated mobile phones offer safety features like: automatically summoning help in case of emergency, automatic hands-free answering and stereo muting to make sure you never miss an emergency call; or voice dialing and speakerphones to keep your hands on the wheel.</P>
<P>Navigation equipment keeps you focused on driving by acting as a copilot who eliminates distracting conventional maps, gives voice directions, acts as a directional pointer, actively reroutes you around traffic problems, directs you to businesses or services, and provides your precise location for emergency services.</P>
<P>See the latest automotive IT products at CES.  Plus hear how mobile electronics manufacturers and retailers are using these new products to further their businesses.</P>
